EUROPE'S CYBER SECURITY FINEST FAILING ON EMAIL SECURITY
Three-quarters of information security leaders attending Infosec are falling short on essential email authentication measures, leaving their trusted brands open to email spoofing. Data-driven cyber security platform Red Sift analysed the DMARC records for exhibitors’ primary email domains.
http://www.businesscloud.co.uk/news/europes-cyber-security-finest-failing-on-email-security

92 Million User Credentials Lost by MyHeritage
MyHeritage, a DNA and genealogy firm, announced Monday that the access credentials of 92 million users had been stolen. It only discovered the breach when a security researcher informed the company he had found a file named myheritage stored outside of MyHeritage.
https://www.securityweek.com/92-million-user-credentials-lost-myheritage

